Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Big projects require thousands of volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.69,0:00:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,over a period of several years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.56,0:00:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,On our program thus far,\Nwe have also considered disaster relief work
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.73,0:00:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and branch renovation projects.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.83,0:00:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these initiatives require
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.97,0:00:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that volunteers fill out an application
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be used in these capacities.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.64,0:00:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are so many avenues of service
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that require the submittal of an application.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.21,0:00:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With that thought in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.22,0:00:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,please carefully watch\Nthe next video entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}A New Application{\r}\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}for Processing Applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.70,0:00:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever submitted\Nan application to expand your ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.04,0:00:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the early 1900’s, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.24,0:00:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,our organization has used paper applications
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.97,0:01:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for many forms of service
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.51,0:01:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and faithful workers have responded.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.75,0:01:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This growth is in fulfillment\Nof Jesus’ words at Matthew 9:37:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.52,0:01:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“The harvest is great.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.09,0:01:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the needs are greater than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.73,0:01:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Can more workers make themselves available?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.27,0:01:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Can applying for different avenues\Nof service be simplified?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.51,0:01:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We are pleased to announce
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.98,0:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,online applications on jw.org®!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.92,0:01:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Publishers will be able to apply {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}online{\r}\Nto expand their ministry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.62,0:01:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Elders will review\Nand approve applications online.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When needed, circuit overseers will review
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.43,0:01:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and approve applications online.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.67,0:02:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your willing spirit\Nto expand your theocratic service
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.60,0:02:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,supports the need\Nfor more workers in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.58,0:02:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah inspired King David to write:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.12,0:02:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your people\Nwill offer themselves willingly.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.66,0:02:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah’s people\Nhave always wholeheartedly responded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.30,0:02:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope this new online tool
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.77,0:02:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you support the Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in whatever way you can,\Nall to Jehovah’s praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.32,0:02:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As you noted,\Nthis provision will be available
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.99,0:02:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for those applying\Nfor various privileges of service
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:03:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning January 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.36,0:03:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Technology continues to make advancements.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.37,0:03:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a way to harness such advances
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.57,0:03:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for the benefit of Jehovah’s people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.44,0:03:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Clive Martin,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,who oversees\Nthe MEPS Department at Warwick,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.31,0:03:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will discuss a new way
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.98,0:03:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to access jw.org® audio files.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.82,0:03:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Brother Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We just love the rich supply\Nof spiritual food on our website and app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.33,0:03:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, some have asked\Nif there’s an easier way to find
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.63,0:03:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and listen\Nto the audio publications and programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.77,0:03:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be particularly helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.07,0:03:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for many of our dear publishers\Nwho have limited vision
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and who depend on these audio programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,With this in mind,\Nwe’re happy to introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.12,0:03:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,jw.org® for Amazon Alexa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.65,0:03:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Google Voice Assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have bought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.26,0:04:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,one of these voice assistants
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to music,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,check the news and the weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.40,0:04:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or perhaps to control your home appliances.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.13,0:04:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can use it to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the content that we need
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.87,0:04:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for our regular spiritual routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.27,0:04:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s try it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.64,0:04:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Alexa, read the daily text from jw.org.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading the daily text.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday, October 5:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Make disciples of people\Nof all the nations, baptizing them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Alexa, play the Bible reading\Nfor this week from jw.org.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.33,0:04:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing this week’s Bible reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.83,0:04:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter of James.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.84,0:04:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.27,0:04:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For Google devices,\Nthe command is just a little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.11,0:04:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s ask for a specific chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:04:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hey, Google,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:05:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,ask jw.org to play Matthew 24.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.85,0:05:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing the Bible\Nstarting at Matthew chapter 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.66,0:05:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 24:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now as Jesus was departing from . . . ”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.10,0:05:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you learning another language?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a feature that can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Alexa,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.37,0:05:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,play the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower {\r} study\Nin Russian from jw.org.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.54,0:05:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing this week’s\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r} study article in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.88,0:05:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.88,0:05:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that your newfound friend\Ndoes have some limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Alexa, what do you think\Nof that new point in {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower?”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.62,0:05:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have an opinion on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s probably just as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.31,0:06:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to listen\Nto the audio track of the monthly broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.81,0:06:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hey, Google,\Nask jw.org to play the broadcast.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.38,0:06:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing JW Broadcasting®, September 2019.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.26,0:06:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.26,0:06:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so happy to have you\Nwith us for this month’s broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.09,0:06:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also ask for the broadcast\Nfor a specific month or year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.96,0:06:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how about some theocratic music?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.83,0:06:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Alexa, play original songs from jw.org.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.34,0:06:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing original songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.12,0:06:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also listen to our collection\Nof Kingdom songs in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if you want to practice\Na specific song for the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.56,0:06:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hey, Google, ask jw.org to play song 57.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.53,0:06:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing 57,\N“Preaching to All Sorts of People.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.61,0:07:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,These features will be available\Nwithin the next few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.69,0:07:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So look on jw.org\Nthis coming week for instructions
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to enable these features\Nfor your Alexa or Google device.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.73,0:07:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank Jehovah and his organization
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.10,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that they make it\Never easier for us to benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from our rich library of spiritual content.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.38,0:07:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We now look forward\Nto Scriptural talks to be presented
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.69,0:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by various members of the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,First, please give your attention\Nto Brother David Splane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:07:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,His subject is intriguing:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.76,0:08:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“An Attack Coming From the North.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.61,0:08:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Alexa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you when I need you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.46,0:08:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, an attack coming from the north—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.80,0:08:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.44,0:08:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we talking\Nabout the attack of Gog of Magog?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.45,0:08:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re talking about an attack
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by a plague of locusts
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:08:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.99,0:09:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can read  \Nabout that plague in Joel chapter 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.83,0:09:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like you to follow \Nand leave your Bibles open, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.56,0:09:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at Joel because we’re going to be considering
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a few verses in this prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.07,0:09:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Joel 2:7-9
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—an attack by a plague,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.08,0:09:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a swarm, of locusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.45,0:09:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Joel 2:7:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.85,0:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“They charge like warriors,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“they scale a wall like soldiers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.69,0:09:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“each keeps to his own course,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they do not swerve from their paths.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.30,0:09:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“They do not shove one another;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.66,0:09:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“each man advances in his course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“If the weapons cause some to fall,\Nthe others do not break ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.50,0:09:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Into the city they rush,\Non the wall they run.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.51,0:09:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Onto the houses they climb,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.54,0:09:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,through the windows they enter like a thief.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.02,0:10:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I think you can see\Nthat we’re not talking about insects here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.19,0:10:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice in verse 8:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Each {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}man {\r} advances in his course.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re talking about people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,who are likened to locusts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.33,0:10:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who have the characteristics of locusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.60,0:10:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Are these good people,\Nor are they bad people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.21,0:10:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,including in the April 15, 2009, {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.98,0:10:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,our understanding was\Nthat these were good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.12,0:10:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, these were Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.39,0:10:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These were Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who were preaching\Nthe good news of the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.43,0:10:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the idea was that they\Nwere just like locusts because,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all,\Nyou couldn’t stop them from preaching
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and they would go to any length\Nto keep preaching the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—probably not go\Ninto people’s windows like thieves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:10:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but otherwise, they’d stop short of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.01,0:11:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But they would do other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.44,0:11:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Preaching the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—it didn’t matter what wall of opposition\Nwas erected against them;
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they would scale that wall\Nand keep preaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.79,0:11:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we were to confine ourselves\Nto a reading of just these three verses,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.62,0:11:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we could make a case for that explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, prophecy is best understood
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when we consider it in context.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.73,0:11:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you look\Nat the context of Joel chapter 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you are forced to come\Nto a different conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.74,0:11:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s consider\Na couple of reasons why this is so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we talk about context,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.98,0:11:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so let’s look at verse 20\Nin the same chapter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Joel chapter 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.42,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And here in verse 20,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re talking about the locusts\Nthat come from the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.56,0:11:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to see\Nhow Jehovah views these locusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.36,0:11:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are these good people,\Nor are they bad people?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:12:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 20:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.70,0:12:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will drive the northerner\Nfar away from you;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.07,0:12:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will disperse him\Nto a dry and desolate wasteland,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.78,0:12:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with his vanguard toward the eastern sea.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.35,0:12:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah is talking\Nabout the locusts here,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.59,0:12:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says he’s going\Nto drive them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.72,0:12:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If these were Kingdom publishers\Nwho are declaring the good news,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.39,0:12:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,why would Jehovah want to drive them away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.93,0:12:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then how does Jehovah view these locusts?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.66,0:12:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the last part of verse 20:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.07,0:12:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“The foul smell from him will ascend,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.20,0:12:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the stench from him will keep ascending.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s looking like these locusts\Nare not good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.92,0:12:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Jehovah talking about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.32,0:12:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pest control.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t like the locusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.22,0:12:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now look at verse 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:12:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.60,0:13:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I will make compensation\Nto you for the years
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“that the swarming locust,\Nthe unwinged locust,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.47,0:13:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“the voracious locust,\Nand the devouring locust have eaten,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.27,0:13:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,my great army that I sent among you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.34,0:13:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, if the locusts\Nwere ministers of the Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.42,0:13:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,why would Jehovah say\Nthat he had to “make compensation”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.95,0:13:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for the damage that the locusts have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The locusts,\Nif they were Kingdom publishers,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.02,0:13:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,would just be helping people\Nto save their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.39,0:13:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So why would Jehovah call that damage?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would he say\Nthey would have to “make compensation”?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.93,0:13:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s one aspect of this\Nthat we considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.07,0:13:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s another one,\Nand that is the sequence of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.91,0:13:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at verse 28,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.51,0:13:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read\Njust the first part of verse 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.25,0:13:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And keep in mind, at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.48,0:13:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has driven the locusts away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.75,0:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They have done all the damage they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They have devastated the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They have destroyed all of the vegetation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.13,0:14:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and now Jehovah God has driven
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.66,0:14:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“the northerner,” the locust, away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.80,0:14:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, what does he say in verse 28?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.93,0:14:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“After that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.14,0:14:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“[after the locusts\Nhave been driven away]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I will pour out my spirit\Non every sort of flesh.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s think about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If the locusts were really carrying out\Nthe preaching work
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.39,0:14:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don’t get the holy spirit\Nuntil after they finish the preaching work,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.82,0:14:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,does that mean\Nthat we’ve been preaching all this time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,without the help\Nof Jehovah’s powerful holy spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’ll all agree,\Nwe couldn’t possibly keep preaching
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.97,0:14:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,without the help\Nof Jehovah’s powerful holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s obvious that we have\Nsome thinking to do about this prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.44,0:14:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, someone might bring up\NRevelation chapter 9,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.68,0:14:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because in Revelation chapter 9,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.88,0:15:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we read of locusts with “human faces”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and what “seemed to be crowns of gold”\Non their heads,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.12,0:15:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and they torment the wicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.89,0:15:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And someone will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, don’t those locusts represent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.33,0:15:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s anointed servants\Nand their preaching work?”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.13,0:15:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.13,0:15:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true\Nthat there are some similarities
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.00,0:15:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,between Revelation chapter 9\Nand Joel chapter 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.47,0:15:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but there are\Nsignificant differences as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.28,0:15:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in Joel’s prophecy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.98,0:15:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the locusts come from the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.05,0:15:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they devastate the vegetation,\Nand they’re driven away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.75,0:15:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about Revelation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.75,0:15:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those locusts come out of an abyss,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.59,0:15:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and “they [are] told\Nnot to harm the vegetation,”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.43,0:15:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and they stay on until their work is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.73,0:15:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are similarities,\Nbut there are also differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We are saying that the locusts in Revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.07,0:16:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are not the same as the locusts in Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.08,0:16:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s not unusual for a symbol\Nto mean one thing in one Bible book
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and something quite different in another
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.95,0:16:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—Revelation 5:5, Jesus,\N“the Lion of the tribe of Judah”;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.96,0:16:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Peter 5:8, Satan the Devil,\N“a roaring lion”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.96,0:16:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—same symbol but quite different meanings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.80,0:16:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.80,0:16:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if the locusts are bad people,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.64,0:16:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if they are not Jehovah’s faithful servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look for a different explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.54,0:16:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.35,0:16:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a simple one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.12,0:16:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Joel is predicting a military attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.12,0:16:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will use Babylonian soldiers\Nwho are just like locusts
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.13,0:16:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—“my great army,” he calls them—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.46,0:16:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring his people into captivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.10,0:16:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And the army is called “the northerner”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.17,0:17:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Babylonians will come up\Nand invade Israel from the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we read Joel 2:8, 9
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.87,0:17:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with the idea of Babylonian soldiers,\Nit all makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.78,0:17:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just read those verses again,\Nverse 8 and verse 9:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.48,0:17:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“They do not shove one another;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.05,0:17:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“each man advances in his course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.89,0:17:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“If the weapons cause some to fall,\Nthe others do not break ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.76,0:17:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“Into the city they rush, \Non the wall they run.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.03,0:17:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Onto the houses they climb,\Nthrough the windows they enter like a thief.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you picture the scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.54,0:17:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There are soldiers everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can escape\Nthe sword of the Babylonians.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.38,0:17:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And this concords\Nwith what the prophet Isaiah wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.51,0:17:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He was looking into the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.18,0:17:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was looking at this event\Nand the outcome of this event.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.02,0:17:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says:\N“All who were found were taken prisoner,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,even though they had fled far away.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.06,0:18:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the prophet Jeremiah\Nforetold something similar
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.80,0:18:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at Jeremiah 16:16.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.80,0:18:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read that; then we’ll go back to Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.28,0:18:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 16:16:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.35,0:18:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Here I am sending\Nfor many fishermen,’
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.85,0:18:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares Jehovah,\N‘and they will fish for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.86,0:18:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘After that I will send\Nfor many hunters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.63,0:18:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and they will hunt them down
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘on every mountain and every hill
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of the clefts of the crags.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.97,0:18:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we used to think\Nthat the hunters and fishers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.41,0:18:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,were hunting and fishing\Nfor righthearted ones
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.18,0:18:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in sort of a marking work, I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.35,0:18:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,where they were looking\Nfor righthearted ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.68,0:18:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, the revised {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}New World Translation{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.22,0:18:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to get\Nthe right understanding of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:18:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice what it says?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“They will {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}hunt them down.{\r}”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the wicked who are being hunted,\Nnot the righthearted ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.16,0:19:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And just to confirm that, look at verse 17:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.03,0:19:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For my eyes are on everything they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“They have not been hidden from before me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.70,0:19:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,nor has their error\Nbeen hidden from my eyes.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in verse 18, he says he is going
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to ‘repay the full amount of their error.’
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.35,0:19:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are not righthearted ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.81,0:19:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people\Nwho might try to hide in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.42,0:19:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll be hunted down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.82,0:19:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If they go out and try to hide in the sea,\Nthey’ll be fished out of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.46,0:19:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They will not get away\Nfrom the Babylonian soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.46,0:19:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But now Joel has some good news for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.23,0:19:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want some good news after this,\Ndon’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the news is restoration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And Joel is saying that at some point\Nan ample supply of spiritual food
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.51,0:19:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to become available for the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.75,0:19:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go back to Joel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.75,0:20:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time\Nread entirely verses 28 and 29.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.85,0:20:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Joel 2\N—Joel 2:28, 29:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.59,0:20:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“After that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.59,0:20:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“[so the Babylonians\Nhave done what they were going to do]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.76,0:20:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will pour out my spirit\Non every sort of flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“and your sons\Nand your daughters will prophesy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.01,0:20:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“your old men will dream dreams,\Nand your young men will see visions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.98,0:20:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“And even on my male slaves\Nand female slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I will pour out my spirit in those days.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.28,0:20:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when was the prophecy fulfilled?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.45,0:20:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.45,0:20:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Peter tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.46,0:20:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was first fulfilled\Nat Pentecost 33 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.46,0:20:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah poured out his spirit,\Nand at the end of that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.50,0:20:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there were 3,000 publishers of the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.34,0:20:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And did Jehovah bless their zealous activity?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.24,0:21:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He certainly did,\Nbecause by the end of the century,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.21,0:21:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands had become obedient to the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.49,0:21:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How many thousands?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.69,0:21:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible doesn’t say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.69,0:21:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do know that it would have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.03,0:21:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot less than 144,000
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.50,0:21:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because the search for Kingdom heirs\Nwas going on in the first century,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.73,0:21:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wasn’t nearly complete\Nby the end of the first century.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.77,0:21:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the zealous activity of those 3,000
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.98,0:21:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who began preaching the good news,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that zealous activity,\Nwas blessed by Jehovah God,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.31,0:21:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and thousands became obedient to the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.05,0:21:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, can we see\Na little bit of a parallel here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.22,0:21:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The year 1919.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1919,\Naccording to official records,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.06,0:21:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there were fewer than 6,000 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.57,0:22:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.07,0:22:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But has Jehovah blessed the efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.04,0:22:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of those 6,000 publishers?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.81,0:22:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of the century,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.61,0:22:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he certainly had shown that he’d blessed\Nthe efforts of the brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.75,0:22:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that every year
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.75,0:22:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,since 1983,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.25,0:22:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 144,000
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.76,0:22:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have been baptized each year?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.79,0:22:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And our brothers today\Ndon’t have the gifts of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.96,0:22:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does this indicate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.97,0:22:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It indicates that Jehovah has made
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.64,0:22:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a mighty outpouring of his spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.61,0:22:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in these last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.64,0:22:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a marvelous thing to behold.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.61,0:22:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when you think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.15,0:22:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we sort of had our explanation\Nbackward in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the past,\Nthe idea was that the spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.42,0:22:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,was poured out in 1919\Nand then the locusts went to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.59,0:22:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because the locusts were Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.72,0:22:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s not what the Bible says, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.79,0:22:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says\Nthat the locusts finish their work,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.36,0:23:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and after that, the spirit is poured out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.96,0:23:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today, thousands upon thousands\Nare getting baptized,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.10,0:23:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can expect that more\Nare going to get baptized in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.67,0:23:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with the new instructions we’ve received:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.67,0:23:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentrate more on conversations;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.34,0:23:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,concentrate more on starting Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.91,0:23:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And with those instructions in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.92,0:23:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,no doubt we’re going to have\Na tremendous increase in baptisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.05,0:23:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, here’s a little word of caution:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.66,0:23:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By all means, have conversations;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.69,0:23:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,by all means, read the Bible to people;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.13,0:23:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by all means, offer Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.23,0:23:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But don’t forget to offer literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.71,0:23:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.71,0:23:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“I deliberately didn’t offer\None piece of literature all month,”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.78,0:23:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re not bragging.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.58,0:23:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we print it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.08,0:23:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And, brothers, let’s be realistic about it:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.62,0:24:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a lovely conversation with someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you don’t find the person\Nfor another three weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.63,0:24:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the person some literature
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.93,0:24:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that he can read\Nso that he can further his interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.17,0:24:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we might think\Nof this explanation and say:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.17,0:24:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, that’s obvious.\NThis explanation is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.14,0:24:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn’t we see it before?”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.08,0:24:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is, yes, it’s obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.98,0:24:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jehovah’s time for us\Nto understand it comes along.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But before Jehovah’s time\Nfor us to understand it comes along,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.69,0:24:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn’t always so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So we always look to Jehovah God\Nfor clarification in matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.63,0:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what has changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.76,0:24:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that in a few lands (but not many)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.30,0:24:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s people do seem to be everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.07,0:24:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as numerous as locusts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.31,0:24:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s true\Nthat in every land we won’t allow
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.28,0:24:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,any wall of opposition\Nto prevent us from doing our work;
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.21,0:25:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re just not doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.22,0:25:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in fulfillment of Joel chapter 2\Nand Jeremiah chapter 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.82,0:25:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s continue having a zealous share
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.49,0:25:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in proclaiming the life-giving message\Nthat God has given us,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.03,0:25:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,confident that he won’t drive us away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.10,0:25:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He will sustain us until the work is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.58,0:25:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was certainly\Nvery encouraging and interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.78,0:25:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Splane.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.91,0:25:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Brother Herd\Nhas something to share with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.42,0:25:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,His title is\N“Study the Bible With the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.16,0:25:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the most important\Nperson that you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.83,0:25:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as dedicated Witnesses of Jehovah,\NI’m sure you would say, “Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.77,0:25:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, who is the second\Nmost important person that you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.24,0:26:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked my wife that once,\Nand she said, “You.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.98,0:26:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she said, “I’m just joking.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.22,0:26:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it’s Jesus Christ, and we all know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.25,0:26:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But, now, how important is it for us to know
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.86,0:26:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,not just Jehovah but also his Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.36,0:26:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s look at something in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.36,0:26:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your Bibles, if you please,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.37,0:26:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to John 17:3,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.17,0:26:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the most familiar scriptures\Nthat we learn when we come into the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.07,0:26:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,John 17:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.04,0:26:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“This means everlasting life,\Ntheir coming to know you,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.55,0:26:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the only true God,\Nand the one whom you sent, Jesus Christ.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.42,0:26:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, let’s think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.42,0:26:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It means our salvation\N—doesn’t it?—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.59,0:26:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to come to know Jehovah God\Nand his Son, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.00,0:26:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to know them\N—it means everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.67,0:27:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our salvation rests on our knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.07,0:27:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah God and his Son, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.94,0:27:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It means our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.55,0:27:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But “coming to know,” what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.48,0:27:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be what\Nthe study note on this verse says?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.42,0:27:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“The verb is used in the present tense\Nto express continuous action.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.43,0:27:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!\NThat’s the correct answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.93,0:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So coming to know Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.97,0:27:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or someone else is an ongoing process.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.31,0:27:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to become\Nacquainted with that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.32,0:27:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if I should ask you,\NHow many of you know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.25,0:27:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise your hands, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.46,0:27:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Get them down because you\Ndon’t really know me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.46,0:28:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, in a sense,\Nyou were right in raising your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.46,0:28:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You know who I am;\Nyou know the position I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.83,0:28:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got my name, you’ve heard me\Ngive some talks, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.37,0:28:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have some knowledge of me,\Nbut there are so many things
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.47,0:28:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,about me that you don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.98,0:28:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you did know these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.88,0:28:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn’t help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.38,0:28:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But, now, coming to know Jehovah\Nis altogether different.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.99,0:28:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming to know Jesus is altogether different.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.42,0:28:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The more we know about them, why, then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.43,0:28:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the better we have a relationship with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.26,0:28:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re going to benefit\Nfrom that knowledge in ever so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.27,0:28:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to come to know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.01,0:28:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how long we’ve been in the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.78,0:28:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,(and some of you\Nhave been there for decades),
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.48,0:28:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we must keep working\Nat coming to know Jehovah God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.32,0:28:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and his Son, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.52,0:28:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But the question is, 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.95,0:29:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we come to know\NJehovah better and better?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.06,0:29:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we can learn much through creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.96,0:29:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We look around us,\Nand it draws us ever closer to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.90,0:29:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When we see the animal creation,\Nas we have earlier today
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.91,0:29:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,(the zebra and various birds\Nand other animals),
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we think of Jehovah and his great wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.68,0:29:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the blessings\Nthat he has showered upon us
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.19,0:29:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of the creation around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.82,0:29:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And how many of us enjoy going\Nto the beautiful parks a certain time of year
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.46,0:29:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoying all the creation\N—the greenery, the flowers, the trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.06,0:29:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My, there’s just no end to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.06,0:29:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And whenever we see fish\Nthat we’ve never seen before
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.84,0:29:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,(and there are so many fish\Nthat are so new to us), 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.47,0:29:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,their beauty—
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.47,0:29:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It all speaks of Jehovah\Nas the Creator, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.48,0:29:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And we marvel at these wonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.95,0:30:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s another way that we benefit:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.45,0:30:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s through his Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.59,0:30:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s through the Bible that we’re able
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.59,0:30:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to know the name of our God—Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.33,0:30:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re able to appreciate\Nwhat that name stands for,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.20,0:30:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re drawn ever closer
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.24,0:30:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to him as a result of that knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.61,0:30:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re able to have\Nthe knowledge of his purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.18,0:30:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that he’s not responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.58,0:30:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for all the wickedness\Nthat goes on in the earth around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.32,0:30:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not of his making,\Nbut yet people in the world feel that it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.49,0:30:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone dies, they blame God:\N“Why did he take that beautiful little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.36,0:30:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“She was only two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.69,0:30:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he do a thing like that?”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.69,0:30:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they have no knowledge,\Nbut you have knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.60,0:30:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When a person dies whom they love,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.77,0:30:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,people in the world have no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.34,0:30:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,about the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.54,0:31:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They feel that two things can happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.64,0:31:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of them feel this way (not all),
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.65,0:31:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that two things can happen\N—either they go to heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.35,0:31:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and become a flower in His garden\Nup there in some kind of a way
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.35,0:31:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or else they go somewhere else
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.89,0:31:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,where they are tormented
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.36,0:31:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,day and night forever and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.13,0:31:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what about God’s Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.53,0:31:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we come to know\Nhim better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.24,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s watch the following video, 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}How Can We Come to Know{\r}\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}the So{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}n {\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}of God Better and Better?, 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.61,0:31:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,seven minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.22,0:31:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He was neither rich nor powerful\Nfrom the world’s point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.92,0:31:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not even have a home\Nthat he could call his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.29,0:31:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, his teachings\Nhave changed the course of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.90,0:31:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They have helped millions to gain
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.07,0:32:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,something more important\Nthan material wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.84,0:32:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The man is Jesus Christ, the Son of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.34,0:32:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants us to know his Son,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.38,0:32:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to love his Son, to be like his Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.15,0:32:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To help us know his Son,\NJehovah lovingly reserved
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.42,0:32:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a portion of his Word, the four Gospels
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.32,0:32:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John—\Nand the book of Acts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.33,0:32:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These Bible books\Nhave helped true Christians to find
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.33,0:32:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the happiest, most meaningful life possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.27,0:32:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gospels portray a man\Nof tender and deep feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.81,0:32:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They show the wide range\Nof Jesus’ personality: 
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.32,0:32:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion for a leper,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.32,0:32:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,indignation at self-righteous\Nreligious leaders,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.32,0:32:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,deep sadness\Nover the nation that rejected him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.33,0:33:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Gospels,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.53,0:33:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn of the many miracles\NJesus performed,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.44,0:33:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,from healing the sick to raising the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.57,0:33:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Those miracles changed people’s lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.81,0:33:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,yet Jesus was not known\Nas Healer or a miracle worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.61,0:33:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he was called the Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.88,0:33:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a teacher he was!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.92,0:33:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the wise sayings\Nof Jesus that have become 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.79,0:33:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,part of everyday speech
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.02,0:33:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of years after he uttered them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.00,0:33:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gospels give\Na fourfold historical account
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.87,0:33:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the life and ministry of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.80,0:33:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew, an apostle, evidently wrote 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.01,0:33:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,his Gospel for the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.41,0:33:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 40 percent of its content is unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.12,0:33:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew gives us a far more extensive account\Nof the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.75,0:34:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In this profound sermon,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.39,0:34:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus does not just tell us\Nthe course of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.26,0:34:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He does much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.26,0:34:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He shows us by explaining,\Nreasoning, and offering proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.33,0:34:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How we marvel at the simplicity, clarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.00,0:34:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and unparalleled wisdom\Nin the teachings of Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.14,0:34:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark’s vigorous, fast-moving account
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.81,0:34:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was seemingly written for non-Jewish readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.72,0:34:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It mentions 19 miracles of Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.65,0:34:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,including the only account\Nof the deaf man whose hearing Jesus restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.69,0:34:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Considerately, Jesus takes\Nthe man away from the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.13,0:34:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and heals him in a private place.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.24,0:34:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How reassuring to learn\Nthat Jesus uses his power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.91,0:34:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in such a considerate and thoughtful way!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.45,0:35:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke, the beloved physician,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.62,0:35:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote for both Jews and non-Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.72,0:35:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some 60 percent of this Gospel is unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.69,0:35:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,including the account of the resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.56,0:35:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the only child of the widow of Nain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.46,0:35:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is “moved with pity” for this widow.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.30,0:35:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After resurrecting her son,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.50,0:35:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus gives him to his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.37,0:35:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Death has torn the family apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.61,0:35:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jesus makes them a family again.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.85,0:35:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How beautifully this account reveals\Na very tender side of the Son of God!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.89,0:35:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,John, the apostle who\Nwas especially close to Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.22,0:35:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote his Gospel last.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.73,0:35:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Some 90 percent contains information
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.93,0:35:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,not found in the other three Gospels.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.03,0:35:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Only John mentions\Nthe resurrection of Lazarus.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.07,0:35:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In this touching account,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.07,0:35:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus openly sheds tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.21,0:36:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How comforting it is to know that Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.61,0:36:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has such deep empathy!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.22,0:36:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, the four Gospels\Npaint a detailed portrait of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.55,0:36:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible book of Acts
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.99,0:36:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,also helps us to come to know Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.93,0:36:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Written by the physician Luke,\NActs is a continuation 
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Gospel of Luke.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.36,0:36:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the opening chapter,\Nwe learn of Jesus’ final words
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.67,0:36:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to his disciples before ascending to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.44,0:36:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The resurrected Jesus leaves\Nno doubt as to what he expects his disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.44,0:36:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,including us, to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.65,0:36:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They are to be witnesses of him
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.05,0:36:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the most distant part of the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.95,0:36:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible book of Acts helps us to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.66,0:36:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what being a follower of Jesus is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.06,0:36:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we benefit fully\Nfrom the four Gospels and the book of Acts?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.77,0:37:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We must do more than just read them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.07,0:37:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We must slow down and take the time
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.17,0:37:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to study them carefully\Nand meditate on them deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.01,0:37:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to bring the accounts\Nto life by doing research,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.71,0:37:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,observing details,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.72,0:37:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,comparing parallel accounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.49,0:37:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and using our imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.09,0:37:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to see, hear, and feel the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.19,0:37:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the years, our organization\Nhas published a number of books
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.53,0:37:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to help us to dig deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.50,0:37:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At the annual meeting in 2015,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.61,0:37:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body announced
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.27,0:37:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that a new online\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}would be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.68,0:37:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How can the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible{\r}\Nhelp us come to know Jesus better?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.52,0:37:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the four Gospels alone,\Nthere are about 2,300 study notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.59,0:38:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Added to that, the image gallery,\Nmaps, and introduction videos
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.26,0:38:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,bring the Bible accounts to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.27,0:38:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no question about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.64,0:38:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Our organization\Nhas given us the help we need 
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.94,0:38:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to dig deeper into the Gospels\Nand the book of Acts
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.04,0:38:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and to reflect appreciatively on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.15,0:38:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, we come to know\Nthe Son of God better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.19,0:38:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We agree with the sentiment\Nof the apostle Peter, 
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.42,0:38:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who said of Jesus: 
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.66,0:38:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Though you never saw him, you love him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.97,0:38:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you benefited from using\Nthe online {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible? 
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.55,0:38:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you will agree\Nthat it is a great tool to help us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.15,0:39:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,come to know God’s Son better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.96,0:39:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if accessing the information online
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.63,0:39:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is not easy for you as an individual?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.86,0:39:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s face it, not everyone has easy access
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.00,0:39:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Internet\Nor finds it easy to navigate online.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.64,0:39:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.64,0:39:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is pleased to announce\Nthe release of a printed version
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.25,0:39:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible 
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.25,0:39:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,containing the five Bible books\Nwe just discussed in the video
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.85,0:39:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—Matthew through Acts.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.06,0:39:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are we releasing\Na printed version of the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible? 
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.90,0:39:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, many prefer\Na printed medium such as a book,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.77,0:39:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,especially for doing\Ndeeper reading and making notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.78,0:39:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easier to slow down
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.85,0:40:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and absorb the information at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.75,0:40:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of us find it easier\Nwhen we use a printed and bound book
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.52,0:40:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for our study periods.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.92,0:40:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever gone back\Nand found something you read in a book
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.96,0:40:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because you recall\Nthat it was either at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.16,0:40:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or bottom of a page
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.40,0:40:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or on the left- or on the right-hand side\Nof a two-page spread?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.14,0:40:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to see\Nwhat this new publication looks like?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.38,0:40:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s watch the next video.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.67,0:41:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some of the features\Nof the printed {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.21,0:41:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that make it an effective tool for studying\Nthe four Gospels and the book of Acts?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.85,0:41:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.02,0:41:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Each Bible book has\Nan introduction with noteworthy facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.86,0:41:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,study notes about the title,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.93,0:41:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and an overview of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.50,0:41:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Subheadings within the sacred text help you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.96,0:41:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to locate specific accounts more easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.00,0:41:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wide margins offer\Nample space for note-taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.97,0:41:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Study notes are found below the scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.71,0:41:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The image gallery\Ncontains 153 illustrations and photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.38,0:41:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from the books of Matthew through Acts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.22,0:41:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The map gallery helps you to combine
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.72,0:41:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,specific events with locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The glossary gives definitions\Nof Biblical and non-Biblical words
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.76,0:41:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that are used in the main text\Nor in the study notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.97,0:42:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to read\Nthe entire Bible in one year?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.47,0:42:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then use the Bible reading schedule\Nto keep track of your progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.04,0:42:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible{\r}\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}is designed to help you study more deeply 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.21,0:42:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring Bible accounts to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.58,0:42:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Take, for instance,\Nthe account of the widow in the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.89,0:42:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 41 says that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.92,0:42:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus “sat down
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.13,0:42:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with the treasury chests in view.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.03,0:42:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.27,0:42:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the study note\Nsay about treasury chests?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.34,0:42:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s interesting:\N‘According to rabbinical sources,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.34,0:42:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there were 13 treasury chests’ for collecting
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.11,0:42:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the contributions\Nof those entering the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.38,0:42:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And these chests were\N“apparently located in the area
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.92,0:42:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,called the Court of the Women.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.19,0:42:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where that was in the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.92,0:42:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.56,0:43:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The study note directs us to Appendix B11.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.20,0:43:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, look at those\Nfour giant golden lampstands!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.47,0:43:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The facade surrounding the front doors
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.17,0:43:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,may have been plated with gold.’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.74,0:43:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.04,0:43:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The “light from the rising sun
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.75,0:43:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,would have been reflected\Nwith dazzling brilliance.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.75,0:43:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to the account.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.45,0:43:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 42 says: “Now a poor widow came
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.09,0:43:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and dropped in two small coins\Nof very little value.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.50,0:43:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the parallel account say?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.73,0:43:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke’s account calls her “a needy widow.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.80,0:43:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The study note says:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.14,0:43:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“Needy . . . may denote a person
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.08,0:43:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“who lacks the basic necessities of life
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.05,0:43:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or someone for whom life\Nis a great struggle.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.02,0:43:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Might the widow have felt that her small gift
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.72,0:44:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was too insignificant to matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.59,0:44:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve felt that way before.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.59,0:44:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus showed that the widow\Nand her contribution
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.36,0:44:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,were valuable to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.63,0:44:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“This poor widow\Nput in more than all the others . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.64,0:44:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She . . . put in everything she had.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.44,0:44:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave her best.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.08,0:44:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When I give Jehovah my best,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.28,0:44:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how much it is,\Nit is precious to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.19,0:44:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible{\r}\Nis designed to help us study
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.76,0:44:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible more deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.00,0:44:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,May this printed edition\Nof Matthew through Acts
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.26,0:44:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,help you to come to know Jesus Christ, 
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.53,0:44:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the Son of God, better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.61,0:45:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that Jehovah set aside
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.85,0:45:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a significant portion of his Word
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.89,0:45:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to become acquainted\Nwith his Son, Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.29,0:45:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—our Ransomer, our Leader\Nand, of course, our King.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.59,0:45:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants us to know his Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.46,0:45:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants us to love his Son
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.87,0:45:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and to put faith in his Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.57,0:45:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So by all means,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.94,0:45:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s—each and every\None of us—use this new Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.91,0:45:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to make progress\Nin coming to know the Son of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.55,0:45:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.55,0:45:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you will also be coming to know better
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.05,0:45:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the One whom Jesus perfectly imitated,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.56,0:45:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,our loving heavenly Father, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.70,0:45:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Brother Herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.37,0:46:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate what we heard from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.74,0:46:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a blessing\Nthe {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible {\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}has proven to be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.25,0:46:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who have it\Navailable in their language.
